Add new features and improve UI for preferences
Integrated a spoiler toggle and redesigned sports order UI in preferences. Added new styles for widgets to enhance visual presentation. Refactored import statements and adjusted button dimensions for better user interaction.

Refactor right_vbox spacers and preferences flow
Replaced the repetitive spacer item with unique named variables for better readability and added a preferences_done method to handle layout clearing. Removed the global variable preferences_done in favor of a method call to improve modularity.

Fix initialization and default values for spoilers
Corrected the default initialization for the `spoilers` attribute in `Prefs` class. Also modified the dictionary comprehension in `prefs.py` for enhanced clarity and correctness.

Refactor spoiler toggle buttons
Refactor the spoiler toggle functionality by replacing the `RadioButton` class with the new `SpoilersButton` class. Updated button style handling and initialization logic for better readability and maintainability.

Add navigation and preference persistence for UI
Introduce QStackedWidget to switch between main menu and preference selection. Implement persistence for user preferences, including defaults, and add navigation logic for transitioning between UI screens.

Add validation for sports selection in preferences page
Implemented a check to ensure users select at least two sports before proceeding to the next page. Adjusted the error message display and modified the size of sports buttons for improved UI consistency.

Refactor button creation to use improved StyledButton class
Replaced direct button instantiations with a new StyledButton class hierarchy for better code organization and reusability. This update consolidates button styling and behavior, reducing redundancy and enhancing maintainability.

Refactor gui_prefs.py to improve code readability
Removed unnecessary comments and redundant imports to streamline the code. This refactor simplifies the structure of the `PreferencesSelection` class and associated functions, leading to better code maintainability and readability.

Add sport and game selection to GUI
Implemented sport and game selection widgets with scroll areas. Integrated these widgets into the main layout alongside existing elements.

Add spoiler and settings button, resize scroll area
Replaced text-based buttons with image-based buttons for spoilers and settings in `gui_main.py`. Increased the scroll area's width and refined scrollbar styles. Enhanced `buttons.py` to include `PictureButton` class and corrected styles and sizes for various buttons.
Spoiler button on main not yet functional...
